<HEAD>NYC Subway Accident Kills Two</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two young men were struck by a train and killed
early today, apparently as they were writing graffiti, police said.
   Cans of spray paint were found near the bodies at the 59th
Street subway station, said Transit Police Officer Joseph Ciociola.
   The victims were about 50 feet south of a waiting platform.
   The train's motorman did not see the young men as he pulled into
the station, but the train braked automatically upon impact,
Ciociola said.
   It was not until he got off the train to see what had triggered
the brakes that the motorman realized the two were there, Ciociola
said.
