<SECOND>PM-Freedom Newspapers,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>Media General to Sell 30 Southern California Weekly Newspapers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Freedom Newspapers Inc. of Irvine, Calif.,
is buying 30 weekly newspapers in Southern California from Media
General Inc.
   The transaction was announced today by Media General. The terms
of the deal were not disclosed.
   The 30 papers have a circulation of 470,000 and are published in
Orange County and eastern Los Angeles County by Golden West
Publishing Inc., a Media General subsidiary. Media General acquired
the newspapers in 1980 and 1981.
   Media General, a communications company based in Richmond,
publishes the Richmond Times-Dispatch, The Richmond News Leader,
the Tampa (Fla.) Tribune and the Winston-Salem (N.C.) Journal. It
also operates TV stations.
   Freedom Newspapers has 27 daily newspapers in nine states and
operates five TV stations.
