<SECOND>AM-Boys Slain,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dodd Pleads Innocent in Three Boys' Deaths</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VANCOUVER, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A paroled sex offender charged with the
murders of three boys pleaded innocent Tuesday.
   Westley Allan Dodd, 28, of Vancouver is being held without bail
on three counts of first-degree aggravated murder, which carries
the death penalty or a mandatory life sentence without parole.
   Dodd admitted in graphic detail to molesting and strangling
4-year-old Lee Joseph Iseli of Portland, Ore., according to an
affidavit filed in court. The boy's body was discovered Nov. 1 near
Vancouver Lake, three days after he disappeared from a schoolyard.
   Dodd also was charged with fatally stabbing Vancouver brothers
Cole Neer, 11, and William Neer, 10, whose bodies were found Sept.
4 in a park.
   Dodd was arrested Nov. 13 after he allegedly abducted a
6-year-old boy from a movie theater and was caught by the boy's
mother's boyfriend. Dodd pleaded innocent to attempted kidnapping
and attempted murder in that case.
   He showed no emotion during the hearing before Clark County
Superior Court Judge Robert Harris, who scheduled trials Jan. 22 in
the Neer deaths and Feb. 26 in the Iseli case and that of the
6-year-old boy.
   Dodd has a history of convictions for sex offenses involving
children that dates to 1982.
