<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert Quigley, who produced game show
classics like ``The Hollywood Squares'' in the 1960s and 1970s,
died after a lengthy illness. He was 77.
   Quigley, who started his career as an actor and writer, forged a
partnership with Merrill Heatter in the early 1960s that resulted
in several efforts, including ``High Rollers,'' ``Gambit,'' ``The
Magnificent Marble Machine'' and ``The Celebrity Game.''
