<HEAD>NEC Net Earnings Rise 27.2 Percent in First Fiscal Half</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NEC Corp., one of Japan's largest computer and
semiconductor makers, posted a 27.2 percent gain in net earnings in
the first half of its fiscal year, the company reported Tuesday.
   Net earnings for the period rose to 33.3 billion yen, about $233
million at current exchange rates, from 26.2 billion yen a year
earlier. Sales for the period climbed 10.1 percent to 1.57 trillion
yen, or $11 billion, from 1.42 trillion yen in the year-earlier
period.
   An NEC spokesman Tuesday said the company expects full-year
sales to rise approximately 8 percent to 3.34 trillion yen, or
$23.4 billion, from 3.08 trillion yen. Net earnings are seen rising
24 percent to 80 billion yen, or $559 million, from 64.4 billion
yen.
