<FILEID>AP-NR-11-28-89 2142EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>d f AM-EC-EnvironmentAgency     11-28 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-EC-Environment Agency,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>EC Founds European Environment Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Environment ministers from the 12
European Community nations on Tuesday approved formation of an
agency to monitor environmental developments.
   The European Environment Agency should be functional by January
1991 if it gets final approval from the European Parliament, said
Carlo Ripa di Meana, the EC's Commissioner for the Environment.
   Ripa di Meana said the agency would collect and interpret
standardized environmental statistics from its member states.
   The information would be used by the EC's executive commission
to establish environmental policy for the trade bloc. Non-EC
countries would be eligible to join the agency but their
applications would be considered on a case-by-case basis.
   Although no budget has yet been fixed for the agency, the
ministers agreed it would be partly financed by the EC's budget and
partly by national budgets of its member countries.
   The agency would be run by a 14-person management board
consisting of a representative of each EC nation and two Commission
representatives. It also would have a nine-person scientific board.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
