<SECOND>AM-Avon-Chartwell,0211</SECOND>
<HEAD>Investor Group Increases Stake in Avon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An alliance of powerful investors including
oil fortune heir Gordon P. Getty said Tuesday it had increased its
stake in Avon Products Inc., the cosmetics company, to 8 percent.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
Chartwell Associates, a limited partnership, said it had purchased
an additional 652,800 Avon shares, increasing its stake from 6.9
percent earlier this month.
   Avon, which previously vowed to fight to maintain its
independence, has twice thwarted unsolicited takeover efforts this
year, including one by Dallas-based Mary Kay Corp. the parent of
Mary Kay Cosmetics.
   A spokesman for New York-based Avon, John Cox, declined to
comment on the latest development.
   Partners in Chartwell Associates include a senior executive of
Mary Kay, the Gordon P. Getty Family Trust and the Fisher real
estate family of New York.
   In the SEC filing, Chartwell Associates said it bought 652,800
shares between Nov. 15 and Monday for prices ranging from $36 to
$37 per share.
   Earlier this year, Avon rejected outright takeover proposals
from the direct sales company Amway Corp. of Ada, Mich., and from
Minneapolis-based investor Irwin Jacobs. Avon also rejected
takeover feelers from Mary Kay.
</TEXT>
