<FIRST>d f BC-AlleghenyInternational     11-28 0234</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Allegheny International,0243</SECOND>
<HEAD>Revised Reorganization Plan Filed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Allegheny International Inc. filed a revised
joint stock plan of reorganization with U.S. Bankruptcy Court on
Tuesday.
   The consumer products company, which manufactures Sunbeam and
Oster small appliances, has been reorganizing under Chapter 11 of
federal bankruptcy laws since February 1988.
   The revised stock plan continues to be jointly proposed by
Allegheny International and its secured bank lenders.
   The plan provides for payment in full in cash of pre-petition
Sunbeam claims, except for certain obligations that are being
reinstated. It also provides for payment in cash of $23.75 million
to Sunbeam institutional lenders in full settlement of all claims
for post-petition interest and other charges.
   Allowed claims of Allegheny International's secured bank group
would be paid in cash to the full extent of cash available. But
Allegheny International management said it does not anticipate any
cash will be available for such distribution.
   As a result, it is expected the secured bank claims class would
instead receive about 59 percent of the reorganized company's new
common stock. It also is believed Chemetron creditors and creditors
of certain other Allegheny International subsidiaries will receive
about 11 percent of such common stock.
   Allegheny International said in a statement the official
committee of unsecured creditors informed the company if will not
support the stock plan.
   The stock plan is expected to take effect around March 31, 1990.
</TEXT>
